Communications Construction Expects 2011 Net to Rise

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-03-10T02:02:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/communications-construction-expects-2011-net-to-rise-correct-.html
(Corrects company name in headline, prediction in first
paragraph).  China Communications Construction
Company Ltd. said it expects 2011 net income to rise to 11.1
billion yuan ($1.7 billion) from 9.44 billion yuan last year
under Chinese accounting standards.  The company forecasts sales to rise to 325.9 billion yuan
from 273.6 million yuan, according to a Hong Kong stock exchange
filing today. Communications Construction will pay a dividend of
0.16 yuan per share for 2010.  The earnings and forecasts were included in a statement
about previously announced plans to sell 3.5 billion A shares in  Shanghai  in a public offering.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  